Functions for calculating rates used for projecting

Edit this page.   Source: R/project_methods.R
project_methods.Rd

The functions defined in the file project_methods calculate the various quantities needed to project the size-spectra forward in time, using the model described in section 3 of the mizer vignette.

List of functions

In this list we relate the functions in this file to the quantities named in the mizer vignette.

FunctionExpressionDescriptionSection in vignette
getRatesAll of the belowgetEncounter
\(E_{e.i}(w)\)Encounter rate3.2getFeedingLevel
\(f_i(w)\)Feeding level3.3getPredRate

\(\mu_{p.i}(w)\)Predation mortality3.7getPlanktonMort
\(\mu_{p}(w)\)Mortality on plankton3.8getFMortGear
